1 hour ago, Esben said:
 
 
As a adult in Paraguay my biggest problem is: are they going to help or they will bring my state to war!?

On the upside though, at least they've already decided on their nationality. Lineage assumption aside I'd imagine the Paraguayans are looking south with a hint of longing and a whole lot of trepidation concerning a new Argentine rival, so they won't really ever care whether Daemon is Paraguayan if he has a surprising way of winning a few battles for Felipe Gonzaga. What's a few thousand civilian deaths compared to the prospect of a lower relative tax rate or being able to immigrate a few lucky folks out of the country?

Good to see you back, @DOB
